// File Watcher
// Watches the diagrams and documents folders for file changes and notifies registered listeners.

Uses chokidar with a write-finish stabilization threshold of 100ms/50ms poll to avoid
partial-write events. Listeners receive a FileChangeEvent with type (created/modified/deleted),
resourceType (diagram/document), id, and path. Watching ignores the initial scan.

FUNCTION FileWatcher.start() -> void                                               EXPORT
  Start two chokidar watchers: one for *.mmd files in DIAGRAMS_FOLDER, one for *.md in
  DOCUMENTS_FOLDER. Each watcher emits created, modified, or deleted events through
  the internal emit method.

---

FUNCTION FileWatcher.stop() -> void
  Close both watchers and clear their references.

---

FUNCTION FileWatcher.restart() -> void
  Stop then start the watchers. Use after changing the storage directory.

---

FUNCTION FileWatcher.onChange(listener) -> void
  Register a listener callback that will be called with every FileChangeEvent.

---

FUNCTION FileWatcher.emit(event) -> void
  Dispatch a FileChangeEvent to all registered listeners.
